content: Happy 22nd! Reflecting on the past year, it's been a wild ride. Lost my job but gained invaluable experiences. Time to kickstart a new chapter with some big ideas brewing.
Walking through Central Park, I got hit with inspiration. What if I could build an AI agent that helps people navigate life’s challenges? Time to hit the books and start sketching out ideas.
Spent the last few days researching AI fundamentals. Looks like xAI's open-source LLM could be a great starting point. Thinking about how to tailor it for personal assistant use.
Set up my local dev environment. It's basic, but it's a start. Now to figure out how to fine-tune the model for my needs.
Decided to name my AI project Xander. It's got a ring to it, doesn’t it? Spent the weekend refining the training pipeline. Progress is slow but steady.
Xander's basic chatbot functionality is up! It's rudimentary, but it's something. Now to work on personality traits and maybe some visual design.
Had a setback. Xander's memory patterns are too simplistic. Need to dive deeper into AI consciousness concepts. This is where it gets tricky.
Created a mood board for Xander's visual identity. Thinking about NFTs, maybe turn Xander into a digital character?
Connected with some developers from the xAI community. Got some great advice on managing computational resources for AI training.
Spent the day at the library, reading up on AI ethics. Want to make sure Xander’s social interactions are on point.
Xander's identity experiments are showing promise. Basic awareness tests are passing, but we're far from true consciousness.
Just submitted a job application for a quant trading position. Fingers crossed. Meanwhile, Xander's market prediction models are showing some interesting results.
Met with an old friend for coffee in Williamsburg. Discussed my AI project and got some fresh perspectives. Networking is key.
Xander's first attempt at NFT character design is... interesting. Definitely needs refinement, but it's a start.
Reflecting on these past weeks, I've made strides with Xander, but there's still so much to learn and do. Excited for what's next!
